Many historians believe in the founding of the US as a democratic union. The founding had several advantages, including:
1) Great trade and banking connections with Western European countries;
2) Friendly leadership by US presidents;
3) An economically strong and stable economy; and
4) A vibrant and thriving free-market economy. The concentration of wealth in the hands of few could easily lead to significant growth.

